📝✍️Scripting is something I did very early in my manifesting career. It worked extremely well. (You should’ve seen the place I was living in compared to my home now.) I’m not sure why I ever stopped doing this but perhaps it’s because I was in exploration.. 

Anyhow, I recently picked it back up and I’m really enjoying having this process back in my routine. 🔥

• Write 1-2 pages AS IF what you want now has already come to fruition. 

• Then re-read it and even re-write it daily. Take your time here. Use a different color pen to trace over what you already wrote.

• Pay close attention to how you feel while reading/writing. And as you go through it see if anything feels off. If so, edit that part of your script to be for the “highest good for all”. 

That’s it. 

I promise it works when done correctly. Get that vibe right though! 😉 

Have you ever done this??

There is a type of intention setting, known as the segment intending. 🙏🏻

When I started using this tool many years ago it was very powerful (and still is today) but I’m so used to using it now that it’s my norm. ✨

Segment intending is where you get super specific about how you want a segment of your life to play out *right before* it actually plays out. 💁🏼‍♀️

So before walking into a meeting at work I’d set the intention for it to be lighthearted, fun, efficient, and end early. 😀

For a difficult customer phone call that I didn’t want to make I’d set the intention for that person to figure out the solution to their problem and no longer needed my assistance. 😌

For my work load, I’d see in my mind the energy of the week/month/quarter calming down and I’d set the intention to be done with everything before it was due 🗓️. 

#Segmentintending is like intention setting but for detailed segments of your life. ✅ 

✔️SAVE THIS POST

To get started, commit to doing it today! 

1. Right before you do something pause for a moment. Example, going into a store, making a purchase at a busy store, waiting in a long line, visiting with friends, cooking a meal, etc. 

2. Before you do what you’re about to do think up what the absolute best outcome would be of your experience. (No wait in a store with long lines)

3. Do not let your logical mind get in the way and try to figure out “how” it will happen. Your job is to imagine the best outcome for this segment. 

4. Release. Let go of it. Enjoy yourself. Move on. 

That’s it! 

✔️SAVE THIS POST so as you practice segment intending you’ll have done notes. 👍🏼

This one was from my 👩‍🎤 mom... and for a very long time I struggled with this. "Who I am is not accepted." was my thinking. "Who I am will be rejected." was my fear. 

Both legitimate. Both incorrect. 

Yes, there have been (and are) many people who do not accept my lifestyle or my beliefs. I no longer feel offended by this because I ACCEPT it. And in my own #selfacceptance I have come to love who I am and appreciate my heart and what I have to offer. So it's no longer a worry for me.

In my acceptance of myself, I have discovered and uncovered relationships who also accept. And really, their acceptance of who I am is just mirroring myself back to myself. See how that works?

Anyways, thanks mom for the quote. Love you infinitely. @morerockit 🚀

In yogic studies it is said that for the first 7 years our personality is forming. We are sponges and our personality/Ego is developed by taking on the personas of those that surround and influence us. (We also develop personas out of need or strong desire.) 

Let's go deep 🕳️ for min... :) and explore a reoccurring thought that I have. 🙌🏼

Have you ever heard of the saying "we are one"? What do you think that actually means? 🤔

Could it be possible that we are all from the same God source/love/consciousness and our personalities are but fragments of personas making up each individual's ego. With some personas being more expressed in some people than in others.

In Conscious Leadership, it's taught that what we see in others is merely a reflection of our selves. So when we see jealousy or hatred in one person/group - we must also look within to see that it is also within us. 

Just thoughts here... would love to hear your take! ⬇️

- Ro
